# Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

We pledge to make participation in this project a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, level of experience, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual orientation.

---

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment include:

- Using welcoming and inclusive language
- Being respectful of differing viewpoints
- Accepting constructive criticism
- Focusing on what is best for the project

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- Harassment, insults, or personal attacks
- Trolling or derogatory comments
- Publishing othersâ€™ private information
- Any form of abusive behavior

---

## Enforcement

Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing standards.
Violations may result in warnings, PR rejection, or bans.

---

## Reporting

Report unacceptable behavior by opening an Issue or contacting the maintainer.

---

This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces.
